Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSchedulingFile(25.10)                              setSchedulingFile(25.10)

Name
       setSchedulingFile - Specifies the name of the scheduling file

Syntax
       setSchedulingFile

       [-help]

       <schedulingFileName>

       Specifies  the  name of the scheduling file. The file is not taken into
       account by CTS, but skewClock must have access to the file if  it  runs
       several times consecutively.

       To  see  the  current  setting  for  the setSchedulingFile command, use
       getSchedulingFile.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each setSchedulingFile parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

               man setSchedulingFile

       <schedulingFileName>
              Specifies the name of the scheduling file.

Example
       The  following command sets the name of the scheduling file to schedul-
       ing_file.cts:

       setSchedulingFile scheduling_file.cts

Related Information
              * getSchedulingFile

